==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Leatherback
<hw>Leath"er*back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large sea turtle (<spn>Sphargis coriacea</spn>), having no bony
shell on its back. It is common in the warm and temperate parts of the
Atlantic, and sometimes weighs over a thousand pounds; -- called also
<altname>leather turtle</altname>, <altname>leathery turtle</altname>,
<altname>leather-backed tortoise</altname>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

